<taxonomicName authority="C. L. Koch, 1836" authorityName="C. L. Koch" authorityYear="1836" box="[151,657,835,862]" class="Chilopoda" family="Scolopendridae" genus="Scolopendra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scolopendromorpha" pageId="5" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="germanica">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,657,835,862]" pageId="5" pageNumber="130">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,439,835,862]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="130">Scolopendra germanica</emphasis>
C. L. Koch, 1836
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1405,907,1078]" box="[151,384,907,933]" pageId="5" pageNumber="130">Original description:</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="130" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1405,907,1078]" pageId="5" pageNumber="130">
<taxonomicName authority="C. L. Koch 1836" authorityName="C. L. Koch" authorityYear="1836" box="[197,656,943,970]" class="Chilopoda" family="Scolopendridae" genus="Scolopendra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scolopendromorpha" pageId="5" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="germanica">
<emphasis box="[197,464,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="130">Scolopendra germanica</emphasis>
C. L. Koch 1836
</taxonomicName>
[1 Oct.]. Index 
<emphasis box="[833,901,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="130">Tab. 2</emphasis>
., Plate 9.2., Text 9.2 [1 page with header 9.2, subsequent page unpaginated] - In: Koch, C.L. (1836a) Deutschlands Crustaceen, Myriapoden und Arachniden. Ein Beitrag zur deutschen Fauna. Herausgegeben von Dr. Herrich-Schäffer, 9 
<emphasis box="[1159,1247,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="130">tes Heft</emphasis>
. Regensburg: Fr. Pustet.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1123,1798]" box="[199,1002,1123,1150]" pageId="5" pageNumber="130">
Parallel publication in 
<bibRefCitation author="Koch, C. L." box="[453,610,1123,1149]" pageId="5" pageNumber="130" refId="ref6618" refString="Koch, C. L. (1836 b) Deutschlands Crustaceen, Myriapoden und Arachniden. Ein Beitrag zur deutschen Fauna. Herausgegeben von Dr. Herrich-Schaffer. 9 tes Heft. F. Pustet, Regensburg, 90 pp. [Author of text and illustrations; the series referred to in the present text as &quot; Koch series &quot;; published 1 October]" type="book" year="1836">Koch (1836b)</bibRefCitation>
(see treatise on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. L. Koch" authorityYear="1836" box="[792,912,1123,1149]" class="Chilopoda" family="Scolopendridae" genus="Scolopendra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scolopendromorpha" pageId="5" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clavipes">
<emphasis box="[792,912,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="130">S. clavipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
above).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1123,1798]" pageId="5" pageNumber="130">
The name 
<taxonomicName authority="C. L. Koch, 1836" authorityName="C. L. Koch" authorityYear="1836" box="[319,672,1159,1186]" class="Chilopoda" family="Scolopendridae" genus="Scolopendra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scolopendromorpha" pageId="5" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="germanica">
<emphasis box="[319,468,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="130">S. germanica</emphasis>
C. L. Koch, 1836
</taxonomicName>
is herewith corrected from the misleading “1837” e.g. in 
<bibRefCitation author="Kraepelin, K." pageId="5" pageNumber="130" pagination="1 - 276" refId="ref7003" refString="Kraepelin, K. (1903) Revision der Scolopendriden. Mitteilungen aus dem Naturhistorischen Museum in Hamburg, 20 (2), 1 - 276." type="journal article" year="1903">Kraepelin (1903)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Attems, C. G." box="[279,444,1195,1221]" pageId="5" pageNumber="130" pagination="2" refId="ref6130" refString="Attems, C. G. (1930) Myriopoda. 2. Scolopendromorpha. In: Schulze, F. E. &amp; Kukenthal, W. (Eds.), Das Tierreich. Vol. 54. Walter de Gruyter &amp; Co., Berlin and Leipzig, pp. 1 - 308." type="book chapter" year="1930">Attems (1930)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1123,1798]" pageId="5" pageNumber="130">
When describing and publishing his 
<emphasis box="[603,902,1231,1258]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="130">
“ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. L. Koch" authorityYear="1836" box="[613,891,1231,1258]" class="Chilopoda" family="Scolopendridae" genus="Scolopendra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scolopendromorpha" pageId="5" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="germanica">Scolopendra germanica</taxonomicName>
”
</emphasis>
in 1836, Koch indicated a possible identity with the earlier described and illustrated “ 
<emphasis box="[564,792,1267,1294]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="130">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Donovan" baseAuthorityYear="1810" box="[564,782,1267,1294]" class="Chilopoda" family="Cryptopidae" genus="Cryptops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scolopendromorpha" pageId="5" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hortensis">Cryptops hortensis</taxonomicName>
”
</emphasis>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Leach, W. E." box="[828,978,1267,1293]" pageId="5" pageNumber="130" pagination="31 - 45" refId="ref7088" refString="Leach, W. E. (1817) The characters of the genera of the class Myriopoda, with descriptions of some species. In: Leach, W. E. (Ed.), The zoological miscellany; being the descriptions of new, or interesting animals. Vol. III. Chapter 12. R. P. Nodder, London, pp. 31 - 45." type="book chapter" year="1817">Leach (1817)</bibRefCitation>
[actually: 
<taxonomicName authority="(Donovan, 1810)" baseAuthorityName="Donovan" baseAuthorityYear="1810" class="Chilopoda" family="Cryptopidae" genus="Cryptops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scolopendromorpha" pageId="5" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hortensis">
<emphasis box="[1098,1311,1267,1294]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="130">Cryptops hortensis</emphasis>
(Donovan, 1810)
</taxonomicName>
] by relating to this reference and followed by a question mark. However, Koch has possibly never seen the reference “Zoological Miscellany” (
<bibRefCitation author="Leach, W. E." box="[553,690,1339,1365]" pageId="5" pageNumber="130" pagination="31 - 45" refId="ref7088" refString="Leach, W. E. (1817) The characters of the genera of the class Myriopoda, with descriptions of some species. In: Leach, W. E. (Ed.), The zoological miscellany; being the descriptions of new, or interesting animals. Vol. III. Chapter 12. R. P. Nodder, London, pp. 31 - 45." type="book chapter" year="1817">Leach 1817</bibRefCitation>
), because he made mistakes with the volume number (II or III) and already in 1836 he called 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Donovan" baseAuthorityYear="1810" box="[443,580,1375,1402]" class="Chilopoda" family="Cryptopidae" genus="Cryptops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scolopendromorpha" pageId="5" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hortensis">
<emphasis box="[443,580,1375,1402]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="130">C. hortensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
“[species] n. 2 [in Leach]” (actually: 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Donovan" baseAuthorityYear="1810" box="[1008,1144,1375,1402]" class="Chilopoda" family="Cryptopidae" genus="Cryptops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scolopendromorpha" pageId="5" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hortensis">
<emphasis box="[1008,1144,1375,1402]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="130">C. hortensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is species no. 
<quantity box="[1309,1353,1375,1401]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="5" pageNumber="130" unit="in" value="1.0">1 in</quantity>
Leach, Vol. III, p. 42, 1817). This concept (
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. L. Koch" authorityYear="1836" box="[549,696,1411,1437]" class="Chilopoda" family="Scolopendridae" genus="Scolopendra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scolopendromorpha" pageId="5" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="germanica">
<emphasis box="[549,696,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="130">S. germanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a synonym of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Donovan" baseAuthorityYear="1810" box="[884,1018,1411,1438]" class="Chilopoda" family="Cryptopidae" genus="Cryptops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scolopendromorpha" pageId="5" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hortensis">
<emphasis box="[884,1018,1411,1438]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="130">C. hortensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) was adopted by prominent researchers like 
<bibRefCitation author="Kraepelin, K." box="[240,432,1447,1473]" pageId="5" pageNumber="130" pagination="1 - 276" refId="ref7003" refString="Kraepelin, K. (1903) Revision der Scolopendriden. Mitteilungen aus dem Naturhistorischen Museum in Hamburg, 20 (2), 1 - 276." type="journal article" year="1903">Kraepelin (1903)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Attems, C. G." box="[485,650,1447,1473]" pageId="5" pageNumber="130" pagination="2" refId="ref6130" refString="Attems, C. G. (1930) Myriopoda. 2. Scolopendromorpha. In: Schulze, F. E. &amp; Kukenthal, W. (Eds.), Das Tierreich. Vol. 54. Walter de Gruyter &amp; Co., Berlin and Leipzig, pp. 1 - 308." type="book chapter" year="1930">Attems (1930)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1123,1798]" pageId="5" pageNumber="130">
Immediately after its description, 
<bibRefCitation author="Gervais, P." box="[582,745,1483,1509]" pageId="5" pageNumber="130" pagination="35 - 60" refId="ref6440" refString="Gervais, P. (1837) Etude pour servir a l'histoire naturelle des Myriapodes. Annales des Sciences naturelles. Zoologie, 2 (7), 35 - 60. [published August 1837]" type="journal article" year="1837">Gervais (1837</bibRefCitation>
, p. 51) synonymized 
<taxonomicName authority="Koch" authorityName="C. L. Koch" authorityYear="1837" box="[988,1206,1483,1509]" class="Chilopoda" family="Scolopendridae" genus="Scolopendra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scolopendromorpha" pageId="5" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="germanica">
<emphasis box="[988,1137,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="130">S. germanica</emphasis>
Koch
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authority="Leach, 1817" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1817" class="Chilopoda" family="Cryptopidae" genus="Cryptops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scolopendromorpha" pageId="5" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="savignii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="130">Cryptops savignii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Leach, W. E." box="[202,340,1519,1545]" pageId="5" pageNumber="130" pagination="31 - 45" refId="ref7088" refString="Leach, W. E. (1817) The characters of the genera of the class Myriopoda, with descriptions of some species. In: Leach, W. E. (Ed.), The zoological miscellany; being the descriptions of new, or interesting animals. Vol. III. Chapter 12. R. P. Nodder, London, pp. 31 - 45." type="book chapter" year="1817">Leach, 1817</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(actually: 
<taxonomicName authority="Leach, 1817" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1817" box="[460,734,1519,1546]" class="Chilopoda" family="Cryptopidae" genus="Cryptops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scolopendromorpha" pageId="5" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="savignyi">
<emphasis box="[460,586,1520,1546]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="130">C. savignyi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Leach, W. E." box="[593,734,1519,1545]" pageId="5" pageNumber="130" pagination="31 - 45" refId="ref7088" refString="Leach, W. E. (1817) The characters of the genera of the class Myriopoda, with descriptions of some species. In: Leach, W. E. (Ed.), The zoological miscellany; being the descriptions of new, or interesting animals. Vol. III. Chapter 12. R. P. Nodder, London, pp. 31 - 45." type="book chapter" year="1817">Leach, 1817</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, because of its prevailing usage: see 
<bibRefCitation author="Lewis, J. G. E." box="[1147,1281,1519,1545]" pageId="5" pageNumber="130" pagination="30 - 35" refId="ref7229" refString="Lewis, J. G. E. (2014) On the status of Cryptops savignyi Leach, 1817, and Cryptops anomalans Newport, 1844 (Chilopoda: Scolopendromorpha: Cryptopidae). Bulletin of the British Myriapod and Isopod Group, 27, 30 - 35." type="journal article" year="2014">Lewis 2014</bibRefCitation>
, Bonato 
<emphasis box="[1380,1429,1519,1545]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="130">et al</emphasis>
. 2016). This classification was also adopted and maintained by 
<bibRefCitation author="Koch, C. L. &amp; Kritische Revision der Insectenfaune Deutschlands von Dr" box="[854,996,1555,1581]" pageId="5" pageNumber="130" pagination="1 - 190" refId="ref6685" refString="Koch, C. L. (1847) Kritische Revision der Insectenfaune Deutschlands von Dr. Panzer and Dr. Herrich-Schaffer, Heft 1 - 190. III. Bandchen, enthaltend die Verzeichnisse und Berichtigungen zu Deutschlands Crustaceen, Myriapoden und Arachniden und ein System der Myriapoden von C. L. Koch [additional title page: System der Myriapoden mit den Verzeichnissen und Berichtigungen zu Deutschlands Crustaceen, Myriapoden und Arachniden. Heft 1 - 40. von C. L. Koch)]. Pustet, Regensburg, 272 pp., 10 pls. [date on title page: 1847, date of preface: 1 April 1846, in the text referred to as &quot; System der Myriapoda &quot;] https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 49866" type="book chapter" year="1847">Koch (1847)</bibRefCitation>
until his last work (
<bibRefCitation author="Koch, C. L." box="[1219,1363,1555,1581]" pageId="5" pageNumber="130" refId="ref6877" refString="Koch, C. L. (1863 b) Die Myriapoden: getreu nach der Natur abgebildet und beschrieben. Band 2. H. W. Schmidt, Regensburg, 112 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 10639" type="book" year="1863">Koch 1863b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1123,1798]" pageId="5" pageNumber="130">
During the following decades none of these taxonomic concepts was unanimously accepted. The classification of 
<taxonomicName authority="C. L. Koch, 1836" authorityName="C. L. Koch" authorityYear="1836" box="[184,543,1627,1654]" class="Chilopoda" family="Scolopendridae" genus="Scolopendra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scolopendromorpha" pageId="5" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="germanica">
<emphasis box="[184,334,1627,1653]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="130">S. germanica</emphasis>
C. L. Koch, 1836
</taxonomicName>
is debated until date. Considered synonyms comprise 
<taxonomicName authority="(Donovan, 1810)" baseAuthorityName="Donovan" baseAuthorityYear="1810" class="Chilopoda" family="Cryptopidae" genus="Cryptops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scolopendromorpha" pageId="5" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hortensis">
<emphasis box="[1171,1308,1627,1654]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="130">C. hortensis</emphasis>
(Donovan, 1810)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Leach, 1817" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1817" box="[231,507,1663,1690]" class="Chilopoda" family="Cryptopidae" genus="Cryptops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scolopendromorpha" pageId="5" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="savignyi">
<emphasis box="[231,357,1664,1690]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="130">C. savignyi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Leach, W. E." box="[365,507,1663,1689]" pageId="5" pageNumber="130" pagination="31 - 45" refId="ref7088" refString="Leach, W. E. (1817) The characters of the genera of the class Myriopoda, with descriptions of some species. In: Leach, W. E. (Ed.), The zoological miscellany; being the descriptions of new, or interesting animals. Vol. III. Chapter 12. R. P. Nodder, London, pp. 31 - 45." type="book chapter" year="1817">Leach, 1817</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and, predominantly, 
<taxonomicName authority="Newport, 1844" authorityName="Newport" authorityYear="1844" box="[750,1085,1663,1690]" class="Chilopoda" family="Cryptopidae" genus="Cryptops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scolopendromorpha" pageId="5" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anomalans">
<emphasis box="[750,906,1663,1690]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="130">C. anomalans</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Newport, G." box="[913,1085,1663,1690]" pageId="5" pageNumber="130" pagination="94 - 101" refId="ref7408" refString="Newport, G. (1844) A list of the species of Myriapoda, Order Chilopoda, contained in the cabinets of the British Museum with synoptic descriptions of forty-seven new species. Annals &amp; Magazine of Natural History, Series 1, 13 (82), 94 - 101. [publshed February 1844] https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 03745484409442576" type="journal article" year="1844">Newport, 1844</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Several relevant references do not mention 
<taxonomicName authority="C. L. Koch, 1836" authorityName="C. L. Koch" authorityYear="1836" box="[296,654,1699,1726]" class="Chilopoda" family="Scolopendridae" genus="Scolopendra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scolopendromorpha" pageId="5" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="germanica">
<emphasis box="[296,446,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="130">S. germanica</emphasis>
C. L. Koch, 1836
</taxonomicName>
at all (
<bibRefCitation author="Lewis, J. G. E." box="[737,874,1699,1725]" pageId="5" pageNumber="130" pagination="11 - 50" refId="ref7161" refString="Lewis, J. G. E. (2011) A review of the species in the genus Cryptops Leach, 1815 from the Old World related to Cryptops (Cryptops) hortensis (Donovan, 1810) (Chilopoda, Scolopendromorpha). International Journal of Myriapodology, 4, 11 - 50. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / ijm. 4.1116" type="journal article" year="2011">Lewis 2011</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Lewis, J. G. E." box="[886,946,1699,1725]" pageId="5" pageNumber="130" pagination="30 - 35" refId="ref7229" refString="Lewis, J. G. E. (2014) On the status of Cryptops savignyi Leach, 1817, and Cryptops anomalans Newport, 1844 (Chilopoda: Scolopendromorpha: Cryptopidae). Bulletin of the British Myriapod and Isopod Group, 27, 30 - 35." type="journal article" year="2014">2014</bibRefCitation>
; Bonato 
